<br>
Seb -- Enchanter messes everything, cleric is at 50% mana, normal group with a wizard, mage, war, wiz, druid, enchanter, two targets are mezed and an extra walks up and there's something that is alomst dead in camp.  Wizard proceeds to AE the area, everything agros that was mezed on the enchanter (2 targets), the unengaged mob agros on the wizard the almost dead target dies.  Wizard starts to get the crap beat out of him, enchanter comes to a sliver of life before everything can be stunned and remezed.  Cleric is now oom, enchanter has been almost cut to ribbons and the wizard is happy because he got to use his AE spell to &quot;help&quot; in killing everything very mana efficiently.  Mind you there are still two mobs mezed and one is being fought.<br>
<br>
This was obviously not the place to use an AE rain, undoubtedly you are going to point out that the wizard was stupid in using it in this case...but that there is my point, there are a lot of stupid people on this server that have no idea what the hell is going on.  An enchanter is forced into saying no to most AE damage spells in close dungeons for that simple fact, people are too stupid to realize the big picture in most cases.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying that everyone gets a red light to AE spell, I just don't trust people that I have grouped with for seldomly and are unpredicatable in my eyes.  This is not to say that we don't trust you, it's just that some people don't play well with enchanters, regardless if you've been grouped with your best friend's cousin's sister.  The last thing an enchanter wants to do when grouping for xp is die, it defeats the purpose. <p>Dauros 55th Enchanter of Ethos<BR>
Taeolin Retired Druid of Brell</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udexn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dexn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 372<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/19/01 9:40:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AoE's Druids, Wizards vs. Enchanters</span><hr size=1> I have no animosity towards wizards.<br>
<br>
A couple of points...<br>
<br>
1. Chanters usually don't get low on mana, unless they're performing double duty for a group. For example, if they're slowing AND hasting AND mezzing. (If they're low on mana outside of these situations, I wouldn't play with that enchanter.)<br>
<br>
2. I don't care what you do, as long as you don't break my mez.<br>
<br>
Sylvaen, 56 chanter o' Brell <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueidolonfaer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eidolon Faer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Dark Lord of Felwithe</span><br>  Posts: 419<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/19/01 10:17:58 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.sprynet.com/~kubik01/eqpics/Sigpic.jpg height=233 width=103></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AoE's Druids, Wizards vs. Enchanters</span><hr size=1> I love AE groups.<br>
<br>
I HATE AE Nukes WHEN I AM NOT PREPARED FOR THEM.<br>
<br>
Understand here:  Enchanters have 8 spell slots just like everyone else.  If I am working in a standard party, I have Mez, Tash, Boon of the Garou, Theft of Thought, a Root, Clarity 2, and Aanya's up.  And a Memblur if I need it.  Maybe a Slow in there too depending.<br>
<br>
If we are EXPECTING the use of AE, I make room for 3 different Color Stuns, and usually RUNE.  It is a totally different spell setup.<br>
<br>
If someone goes around AE blasting without LETTING ME KNOW then I become utterly useless and usually dead.  If you tell me ahead of time I can change my setup and we can party down.<br>
<br>
That's why Enchanters get pissed.  Sitting down to swap out 4 spells with 12 MOBs on the party is horribly inconvenient.  Especially when 11 of them are aggroed on ME because a Mez was broken.<br>
<br>
Also, you need to consider the party makeup and the local MOBS before going AE.<br>
<br>
I love good AE groups.  I hate a Wizzy or Dr00d who decides to Supernova or Earthquake with no warning when there are 4 Mezzed MOBS in camp.  Understand the distinction?<br>
<br>
Eidolon Faer<br>
Enchanter of the 54th Confusion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrungleeisenguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krungle Eisenguss</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/19/01 11:35:42 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AoE's Druids, Wizards vs. Enchanters</span><hr size=1> This is in reply to Dauros.<br>
<br>
Dauros, by your own words you are biased against Wizards:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    &quot;people are too stupid to realize the big picture in most cases.&quot; ....&quot;I just don't trust people that I have grouped with for seldomly and are unpredicatable in my eyes.&quot; </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Give the poor Nuker a chance to do his job. By the above quotes, I do not believe you do so. I cannot see you at your level telling a new tank to your group to &quot;please make an assist hotkey to target &lt;main puller&gt;.&quot; However, I can see you climbing all over a Wizard that AoE's, even if it is a good one by saying &quot;No more AoE's or I leave!&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    &quot;Enchanter messes everything&quot;...&quot;everything agros that was mezed on the enchanter&quot; </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The Wizard uses a DD AoE. This should do between 15-30% damage to all the MoBs. This really pisses off the MoBs. The MoBs agro the Wizard, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the Enchanter. Only reason a MoB would agro the enchanter is if it resisted the Nuke. This is also why the Wizard <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   must</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> have his &quot;Magic Skin&quot; on and Root memmed. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    &quot;an extra walks up&quot; &amp; &quot;This was obviously not the place to use an AE rain&quot; </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
This argument is known as &quot;The Strawman Argument&quot; and the person that coined that term would not even answer such an autrocity. I will, however. <br>
<br>
First, the spell to kill one MoB and activate the second is a DD AoE, as I had stated, but perhaps not clearly enough for you. This makes your second quote moot, null <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  and</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> devoid of any meaning.<br>
<br>
Second, being in a group means you are going into a dangerious area where things can go wrong. &quot;an extra walks up&quot; is just such an &quot;Oh, $4it!&quot; situation. But, if such happens while the Wizard is casting his AoE, then there is no way in the Plane of Chaos that an Enchanter is going to stand up, target a new MoB, and Mez it before the DD AoE goes off. Again, you presented an arguement with no merit.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    &quot;The last thing an enchanter wants to do when grouping for xp is die, it defeats the purpose.&quot; &amp; &quot;Cleric is now oom&quot; </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The assumption here is the good Wizard does not care if people die. Again, this shows your anti-Wizard bias. The Wizard's job is to do serious damage to MoBs so they die quickly. This means the MoBs have less time to do damage to the tanks. Less damage to tanks = less heals = less downtime for the Cleric = faster pulls = better Exp.<br>
<br>
I would like to end this response with the quote it began on:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    &quot;people are too stupid to realize the big picture in most cases.&quot; ....&quot;I just don't trust people that I have grouped with for seldomly and are unpredicatable in my eyes.&quot; &amp; &quot;The last thing an enchanter wants to do when grouping for xp is die, it defeats the purpose.&quot; </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
If this is the cases that you have run into in your groupings, then maybe you are grouping with the wrong people. Or, you are just Anti-Wizard biased. <br>
<br>
