<br>
I'm sure you'll quote the numbers at me, but I'm sure that the traditional single assisted target approach is more controlled and mana-efficient: you concentrate all your efforts on one target and drop that quickly. The tanks can usually taunt the mob enough to keep handwavers' spells from being interrupted, and the Cleric only has one or two health bars to watch to keep the group alive.<br>
<br>
